# {{.ProjectName}}

OpenCode workspace-config scaffold generated by [plugin-kit-ai](https://github.com/777genius/plugin-kit-ai) `init`.

This lane models the official OpenCode workspace config surfaces that fit the package-standard authoring model today.

## Status

- Target lane: `opencode`
- Platform family: `code_plugin`
- Launcher: not used
- Runtime claim: config/workspace lane only

## First Run

```bash
plugin-kit-ai generate .
plugin-kit-ai generate --check .
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform opencode --strict
```

## Target Files

- `src/plugin.yaml`: canonical shared plugin metadata and target list
- `src/targets/opencode/package.yaml`: authored OpenCode package metadata; `plugins` renders to `opencode.json.plugin` as strings or `[name, options]` tuples
- `src/targets/opencode/default_agent.txt`: first-class `opencode.json.default_agent`
- `src/targets/opencode/instructions.yaml`: first-class `opencode.json.instructions`
- `src/targets/opencode/permission.json`: first-class `opencode.json.permission`
- `src/targets/opencode/config.extra.json`: sanctioned fallback for broader OpenCode config outside the first-class authored contract
- `src/mcp/servers.yaml`: portable MCP authored source; `plugin-kit-ai init --extras` pre-seeds a starter and generate projects it into `opencode.json.mcp`
- `src/targets/opencode/commands/`: markdown commands mirrored into `.opencode/commands/`
- `src/targets/opencode/agents/`: markdown agents mirrored into `.opencode/agents/`
- `src/targets/opencode/themes/`: JSON theme definitions mirrored into `.opencode/themes/`
- `src/targets/opencode/tools/`: standalone JS/TS tool definitions mirrored into `.opencode/tools/`
- `src/targets/opencode/plugins/`: local JS/TS plugin subtree mirrored into `.opencode/plugins/`
- `src/targets/opencode/package.json`: shared dependency metadata mirrored into `.opencode/package.json` for standalone tools and plugin code
- portable `src/mcp/servers.yaml`: canonical human-authored portable MCP source
- portable `src/skills/`: validated against the shared `SKILL.md` contract, then mirrored into `.opencode/skills/`
- root `CLAUDE.md` and `AGENTS.md`: boundary docs that tell humans and agents to edit only `src/`
- `opencode.json`: generated managed OpenCode workspace config

## Current Boundary

- Supported in v1: plugin package refs including tuple-form options, shared MCP, portable skills, workspace commands, workspace agents, `default_agent`, `instructions`, `permission`, workspace themes, local JS/TS plugin subtree import/generate/validate, plugin-local dependency metadata, JSON/JSONC native config import, explicit `--include-user-scope` import
- Beta-only in v1: standalone `.opencode/tools/**` authoring and the broader custom-tools capability across standalone tools and plugin code
- Canonical local plugin starter shape: official-style named async plugin exports; canonical standalone tool starter shape: `export default tool({...})`; helper-based tools and plugins require `@opencode-ai/plugin` in `targets/opencode/package.json`
- Native OpenCode config can be imported from `opencode.json` or `opencode.jsonc`; authored skills must live under `src/skills/**`
- Broader product config still stays under `src/targets/opencode/config.extra.json`; deprecated top-level `mode` is imported as an alias for `agent`, and config-level `tools` settings remain distinct from first-class standalone tool files under `src/targets/opencode/tools/`
